<!-- post # 2 --><font color="#FF0000">MEMORIES OF VIET NAM</font><br><tt>Mon Nov 11  1:06:50 US/Eastern 1996</tt><p>I have not yet been.  I tell my wife I want to go.....will I ever be there.....I do not know.....<br>My politics are certainly different than before.  I trust no politicians.  <br>My sons will never fight a war, but I know the future is not certain for my grandsons.  I feel a great frustration, knowing that we, the people of our nation, have no individual way of preventing our involvement in another great war. Yet I do not want us to organize and make a strong determination that our country not retain war as an option.  I will always have bittersweet memories of that time...and of the friends made and lost....<p><code>-- rbrssard@alaska.net  (Roy Broussard) </code><p>